org.mindswap.owls.process.execution
Interface ExecutionValidator

All Known Implementing Classes:
StandardExecutionValidator
public interface ExecutionValidator

An execution validator is used in the course of (composite) process execution to validate preconditions and results. Depending on the logic language used to express those preconditions and result effects, various implementations may exist. If such a logic language is not automatically decidable it is even imaginable to implement a validator that integrates humans in the loop of validation (by means of whatever kind of user interface that allows the user to state if some precondition is satisfied respectively some result is valid).

Method Detail

checkPreconditions

void checkPreconditions(Process process,
                        ValueMap<ProcessVar,OWLValue> values,
                        OWLKnowledgeBase kb)
                        throws ExecutionException
Parameters:
process - The process whose execution will be done next.
values - The set of process variable bindings that exist at the time of precondition evaluation. Since precondition evaluation happens prior to execution the map would contain only inputs bound to their value. Note that evaluation of preconditions may bind existential process variables (if any). If so, implementations of this method must put them in this map.
kb - All the (domain) knowledge available right now.
Throws:
UnsatisfiedPreconditionException - In case isPreconditionCheck() returns true and some precondition of the given process is not satisfied.
MultipleSatisfiedPreconditionException - In case isPreconditionCheck() returns true, isAllowMultipleSatisifedPreconditions() returns false and some precondition of the given process has multiple different "solutions", i.e., it can be satisfied by different bindings of variables in the precondition.
ExecutionException

checkResults

void checkResults(Process process,
                  ValueMap<ProcessVar,OWLValue> values,
                  OWLKnowledgeBase kb)
                  throws ExecutionException
Parameters:
process - The current process whose execution was done and whose result(s) are to be evaluated.
values - The set of process variables that exist in the scope of the given process. In case of result evaluation this can be inputs that were consumed by the process, outputs produced by the process, locals used within the process, and existentials bound by preconditions.
kb - All the (domain) knowledge available right now.
Throws:
ResultException - In case application of the effects of some result caused the kb to become inconsistent.
ExecutionException

setAllowMultipleSatisfiedPreconditions

void setAllowMultipleSatisfiedPreconditions(boolean allowMultipleSatisfiedPreconditions)
Set the behavior that determines if evaluation of a precondition that can be satisfied by multiple different bindings of variables occurring in the precondition is regarded a evaluation failure or not. If this option is enabled then in such a situation the execution engine will arbitrarily pick a value from any of the different bindings that exist and continue.

Parameters:
allowMultipleSatisfiedPreconditions - If true multiple value bindings for variables used in preconditions is allowed. If false then such a situation would cause throwing a MultipleSatisfiedPreconditionException.

setPreconditionCheck

void setPreconditionCheck(boolean checkPreconditions)
Enable/disable precondition validation. Note that if there are existential variables bound by the precondition then the overall execution may fail when precondition evaluation is disabled, in particular if the are required for result evaluation.

setResultCheck

void setResultCheck(boolean checkResults)
Enable/disable result (effects) validation.
